{
  "_resourceType": "script",
  "id": "7aeaa8f6-95c3-4304-a875-de03386607cd",
  "name": "StartPsychicScan",
  "description": "Holding B sends Muckle into psychic trance, scanning for a robot in range. Contains a while loop so we can hold this state while B button is held. If B is released, StopPsychicScan script is called to cancel scanning.  If UP is pressed while B is still held, StartPsychicControl is called to pass control to Robot. Then, B will call StopPsychicControl.\n\nThere a lot of scripts being attached to and removed from Buttons during this sequence for various reasons. This is the core script-attaching chain for psychic control:\n1.) StartPsychicScan must be called as an attached script on B button on scene Init.\n2.) If there's a Robot in range, this script attaches the StartPsychicControl script to the UP button. \n3.) If UP is pressed, StartPsychicControl script attaches the StopPsychicControl script to the B button.\n4.) StopPsychicControl then re-attaches StartPsychicScan to the B button.",
  "variables": {},
  "actors": {},
  "symbol": "script_1",
